    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="934"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d934">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Additional inquiry from Spanish Government just received through British minister
                    for foreign affairs as to whether Transatlantic Company steamer <hi
                        rend="italic">San Augustin</hi> now at San Martinique fitted as hospital
                    ship, with medical officers aboard, can be used to transport wounded to Spain.
                    If request is granted the vessel will be sent immediately to Santiago de Cuba
                    under same previously proposed conditions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
